    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI'm running neovim on Arch Linux and recently installed v0.12 which introduced a regression where my backspace key records a backspace on both keydown and keyup events, resulting in every keypress deleting two characters while in insert mode.\n\nI built from source and the issue is not present on the v0.11.7 tag, but exists on the v0.12.0 tag. Bisecting reveals this commit causes the issue: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/466f20dd7039e1602c9382f76ac6471d9feb49b7.\n\nI'm able to revert that commit on master and produce a development build without the issue. This is in the Alacritty terminal, the issue is not present in Konsole.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\ngit checkout v0.12.0\nmake clean distclean && make CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=RelWithDebInfo && build/bin/nvim --clean\nenter insert mode and write \"asdf\", then press the backspace key once - 'f' is removed on keydown, and 'd' is removed on keyup\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nonly 'f' should be removed 😄 \n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\ndid not test vim\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux 6.19.11-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.14.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nTERM=alacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuilt from source",
